Instead of the grid reacting only after a primary power plant fails, this distributed network would continuously monitor the derivative of the grid's total stability.

59:08.480 --> 59:23.180
If a massive heat wave strikes, and the primary power plants acting as their thermal core begin to suffer thermal collapse, the decentralized network detects the exact negative slope of the decline in milliseconds.

59:23.360 --> 59:24.900
Before the lights even flicker.

59:24.900 --> 59:25.640
Precisely.

59:25.640 --> 59:36.020
Before the AC frequency even drops, millions of home batteries instantly inject microbursts of power into the exact localized neighborhoods that are failing the fastest.

59:36.240 --> 59:37.460
Catching the falling plate.

59:37.700 --> 59:37.980
Yes.

